Label: MUTYH-3
Comment: This isoform of MUTYH uses exon 1-alpha and the exon 3 splice donor site variant-3. This is one of the most abundant MUTYH transcripts, while the transcripts that corresponds to the canonical UniProt sequence and to the longest NCBI transcript of MUTYH are rare or not present (Plotz et al. 2012).

Label: Formation
Comment: Base excision repair is initiated by DNA glycosylases that hydrolytically cleave the base-deoxyribose glycosyl bond of a damaged nucleotide residue, releasing the damaged base (Lindahl and Wood 1999, Sokhansanj et al. 2002).
